|YK0#|YKB Guild and Class Equipment Guidance|000

|GK0Guild and class equipment rules are checked when you try to wear armour or
wield a weapon. These are practical guidelines for normal equipment; special
items can still directly allow or restrict specific guilds or classes.|000

|CKBImportant notes|000
|GK0- Specific bans are checked before specific allows.
- Specific allows are checked before broad bans.
- Item-level guild or class allow/restrict flags override the normal table.
- Size, damage type, armour composition, slot, and material can all matter.|000

|YK0##|YKB Guilds|000

|CKBFighter|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: any normal armour or shield.
Materials: no normal material restriction.|000

|CKBPaladin|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: any normal armour or shield.
Materials: no normal material restriction.|000

|CKBBard|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: no plate, scale, or shields.
Materials: no normal material restriction outside those armour types.|000

|CKBCleric of Mitra|000
|GK0Weapons: blunt weapons only. Slash, cleave, and pierce weapons are not
allowed.
Armour: any normal armour or shield.
Materials: no normal material restriction.|000

|CKBPriest of Set|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: no plate armour.
Materials: no normal material restriction outside plate armour.|000

|CKBGarou|000
|GK0Weapons: avoid magical, missile, silver, and most metal weapons. Polearms
are the normal weapon exception.
Armour: avoid magical, silver, plate, and metal armour. Rings and amulets are
explicitly supported. Some Gaea-touched auras are specially allowed.
Materials: silver is forbidden; most metal equipment is forbidden unless a
specific exception applies.|000

|CKBMage|000
|GK0Weapons: no medium, large, or huge slash, pierce, or cleave weapons. Small
weapons, blunt weapons, focus-style items, and other non-blade options are the
safer choices.
Armour: no plate or shields. Padded cloth, leather boots, leather gloves,
leather cloaks, rings, and amulets are explicitly supported.
Materials: broad armour restrictions hit metal, leather, rock, and wood unless
a specific allowed slot/material exception applies.|000

|CKBNecro|000
|GK0Uses the same normal equipment profile as Mage.
Weapons: avoid medium or larger slash, pierce, and cleave weapons.
Armour: no plate or shields; light cloth/leather utility slots are safest.
Materials: broad armour restrictions hit metal, leather, rock, and wood unless
a specific allowed exception applies.|000

|CKBBlood Mage|000
|GK0Uses the same normal equipment profile as Mage.
Weapons: avoid medium or larger slash, pierce, and cleave weapons.
Armour: no plate or shields; light cloth/leather utility slots are safest.
Materials: broad armour restrictions hit metal, leather, rock, and wood unless
a specific allowed exception applies.|000

|CKBThief|000
|GK0Weapons: no large, huge, or pole weapons.
Armour: small shields, rings, amulets, hide, padded, and studded armour are
explicitly supported. Avoid plate, scale, chain, banded, and most shields.
Materials: avoid metal, rock, glass, and crystal armour unless a specific
allowed type applies.|000

|CKBNinja|000
|GK0Weapons: no large or huge weapons in general. Polearms and blunt weapons
are explicit exceptions.
Armour: no shields. Rings, amulets, and auras are explicitly supported. Avoid
plate, scale, banded, and chain.
Materials: avoid metal armour unless a specific allowed slot applies.|000

|CKBSwashbuckler|000
|GK0Weapons: no huge weapons, large cleaving weapons, missile weapons, or
polearms.
Armour: no plate or shields. Amulets, boots, hide, padded armour, and rings are
explicitly supported. Avoid banded, chain, scale, plate, and shields.
Materials: avoid crystal, glass, metal, rock, and wood armour unless a specific
allowed type applies.|000

|YK0##|YKB Additional guilds|000

|CKBDruid|000
|GK0Weapons: nature-friendly gear is safest. Small weapons, large or huge blunt
weapons, missile weapons, polearms, and weapons made from rock, natural, wood,
bone, glass, crystal, gold, or gem materials are explicitly supported. Avoid
metal medium weapons and metal slash/cleave/pierce weapons.
Armour: small shields, rings, amulets, and wood, rock, natural, bone, glass,
crystal, gem, gold, or silver armour are explicitly supported. Avoid large and
huge shields, and avoid metal plate, chain, scale, banded, and shields unless a
specific material exception applies.
Materials: natural materials are best. Metal is usually trouble; gold and
silver have specific armour exceptions.|000

|CKBRanger|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: no plate or scale. Studded leather, studded cloth, magical chain,
rings, and amulets are explicitly supported.
Materials: no broad material restriction outside the plate/scale armour ban.|000

|CKBMonk|000
|GK0Weapons: only the supported staff-like profile is allowed: medium polearm
and blunt.
Armour: only auras are allowed.
Materials: all normal weapon and armour materials are restricted unless the
item fits the allowed weapon profile or aura slot.|000

|CKBBerserker|000
|GK0Weapons: any normal weapon.
Armour: light, medium, or heavy armour, including shields.
Materials: no normal material restriction.|000

|YK0##|YKB Classes|000

|GK0Class restrictions reflect what a character innately is rather than a
learned guild discipline.|000

|CKBPsionicist|000
|GK0Weapons: avoid large and huge weapons, especially slash, pierce, and cleave
weapons. Blunt polearms with the supported size/type combination are the
notable exception.
Armour: no helmets, plate, chain, scale, banded, or shields.
Materials: leather, natural, and cloth armour are explicitly supported.|000

|CKBMorpher|000
|GK0Weapons: no large, huge, or missile weapons.
Armour: no plate or chain.
Materials: no normal material restriction outside those weapon and armour
types.|000

|YK0##|YKB Quick material reminders|000

|GK0Metal includes steel, iron, silver, gold, mithril, adamantite, bronze,
brass, tin, lead, copper, and platinum.
Natural-friendly materials usually include natural, wood, rock, bone, glass,
crystal, gem, cloth, leather, skin, fur, flowers, and similar non-metal
materials, though each guild or class still checks slot and armour/weapon
type.|000

